<p><b>Pablo Emilio Escobar Gaviria</b>, (1 December 1949 - 2 December 1993), gained world <a href="/wiki/Infamy" title="Infamy">infamy</a> as a <a href="/wiki/Colombian_People" title="Colombian People" class="mw-redirect">Colombian</a> <a href="/wiki/Drug_lord" title="Drug lord">drug lord</a> and became so wealthy from the drug trade that in 1989 <a href="/wiki/Forbes" title="Forbes"><i>Forbes</i> magazine</a> listed him as the seventh richest man in the world.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
